From Subject Maria Goretti Heres the life of MAria Goretti posted with kind permission of the editor of the Australian Catholic Magazine Morning Star Hope you like Put up with anything to prevent sin Maria Goretti Maria was born on October to Luigi and Assunta Goretti the eldest daughter in the family of She was a cheerful girl always imitating her She had but one disire but one wish to receive our Lord in the Blessed The date was finally set for little Maria to receive our Lord on the feast of Corpus For Maria time seemed like an eter nity as she slowly neared the great When it finally arrived Jerome the priest who was to celebrate the Mass and give the children their First Holy Communion delivered a sermon on the immense love of Jesus Christ for them and the great love we should have in return for He then warmly urged them to die rather than commit a mortal Maria humbly approached the Altar of God and received the Holy Her only sadness was the thought of her father's absence who died some time As for the rest of the day Maria remained under the spell of the divine visit that is until her thoughts changed to when she could go next to Holy Thus ended the happiest day of Maria's Over the next twelve months Maria had changed from a giggling little girl into a quiet young lady with As her mother went out into the fields in place of her husband Maria took on the ironing cooking washing and other motherly She was doing this not only for her own family but also for the Serenellis a father and son who lived with the Goretti's owning a share in the Although Maria was poorer than all the other children she by far surpassed them in In all thi ngs she did the Holy Will of During the month of June Alessandro Serenelli the son twice made advances upon Maria when he chanced to be alone with On both occasions Maria managed to struggle free of Alessandro's strong grip but on the second he threatened to kill her if she even uttered a word to her From this day on Maria lived in terror fearing lest Alessandro attack On July Alessandro left work in the fields to get a handkerchief as he He went to the storeroom beneath the house where Maria who was outside on the landing with the baby could hear him fumbling about in with She wondered what he was It was later learned that he was sharpening a He went to the house and called for She told him she wouldn't go to him unless she knew why she was He stormed out to the landing and dragged her up to her Mar ia instantly realized what he was up No No No Do not touch me It is a sin you will go to Hell At this point Alessandro held the knife over Maria's chest who was now on the Will you or will you not Maria gathered all her No I will not Alessandro no She had chosen her martyrdom over sin God over Overcome with rage Alessandro plunged the knife into Maria's breast fourteen Finally he came to his senses and thought Maria was Frantically he threw the knife behind a closet and locked himself in his The crying of the baby Teresa on the landing brought the attention to Assunta and the father of As the baby was unattended and was in danger of falling off they ran to the house to find Maria who covered in blood was dragging herself to the When asked what happened she said Alessandro stabbed He wanted to make me do wrong and I would The ambulance arrived then the police who took Alessandro As the ambulance carried Maria to the hospital a large crowd followed on The doctors at the hospital held no hope for poor little The same Jerome who gave Maria her First Communion came to administer the last rites and to give her Holy He asked Maria if she would forgive her For the love of Jesus I forgive I wish for him to one day join me in May God forgive him for I alread y Maria died at about three o' Alessandro was tried and found guilty of Maria's death but because of his age he was sentenced to only thirty years in After eight years of being a violent prisoner and show ing no regret for his crime he saw in a dream in the midst of a field of flowers Maria holding out a bunch of white lilies to Soon later he wrote to the local bishop begging God's par don for the grave sin he had He later gave testimony in Maria's beatification in Less than three years later on Ju ne Maria was Assunta Goretti was the first mother ever to be present at her daughter's May Maria Goretti help us to be pure and grant us the strength to die rather than commit a mortal Saint Maria Goretti pray for by Brendan Arthur Internet Viva Cristo Rey Long Live Christ the